				     MongoDB

* MongoDB is an open source database that uses a document-oriented data model.It doesnt work on relations.
* We have to create collections for storing data.There is key field  which represent attribute of collection.
* For each collection there is _id object.We can create multiple collections within one collection.
* It provised flexibility for accessing data.
* Embedded documents and arrays reduce need for joins.
*Database holds a set of collections.collection holds a set of documents.document is a set of key-value pairs.

